name: AFRICAN STAR APPLE(Agbalumo)
description: The African Star Apple is a fruit native to West Africa and is particularly prolific in Nigeria, Republic of Benin, Togo and Ghana. Agbalumo, Udara, Udala etc.african star apple(agbalumo)the African star apple is a rich source of calcium, with each serving providing up to 10% of the recommended daily allowance (RDA). The fruit also contains good amounts of vitamins A and C (higher, in fact than levels found in oranges or guava). Star apples are also quite rich in iron.Yeah, some fruity art for you to enjoy..
